Wine Reviews¶

首先，将文件存入数组中，便于后续处理：¶

In [ ]:
import os

def file_filter(f):
        if f[-4:] in ['.csv']:
            return True
        else:
            return False

def get_file_list(dir_):
    lists = os.listdir(dir_)
    lists = list(filter(file_filter, lists))
    return lists

file_path_arr = get_file_list(os.path.abspath(os.curdir))
print(file_path_arr)

['winemag-data-130k-v2.csv', 'winemag-data_first150k.csv']

['Unnamed: 0' 'country' 'description' 'designation' 'points' 'price' 'province' 'region_1' 'region_2' 'variety' 'winery']

13

Unnamed: 0

countryThe country that the wine is from

description

designationThe vineyard within the winery where the grapes that made the wine are from

pointsThe number of points WineEnthusiast rated the wine on a scale of 1-100 (though they say they only post reviews for wines that score >=80)

priceThe cost for a bottle of the wine

provinceThe province or state that the wine is from

region_1The wine growing area in a province or state (ie Napa)()

region_2Sometimes there are more specific regions specified within a wine growing area (ie Rutherford inside the Napa Valley), but this value can sometimes be blank()

varietyThe type of grapes used to make the wine (ie Pinot Noir)()

winery

taster_name

taster_twitter_handle

titleThe title of the wine review, which often contains the vintage if you're interested in extracting that feature

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def hist_bar(index, number, whole_data_):
        plt.figure(figsize=(40, 5))
        plt.title(file_path_arr[index])
        X = whole_data_[index][attribute].value_counts().index[:number]
        Y = whole_data_[index][attribute].value_counts().values[:number]
        plt.bar(X, Y, edgecolor='black')
        for x, y in zip(X, Y):
                plt.text(x, y, '%d' % y, ha='center', va='bottom')

def figure_by_attribute(file_index, attribute, whole_data_):
        print("current file name: ", file_path_arr[file_index])
        current_data = whole_data_[file_index]
        bin_data = current_data[attribute].value_counts(dropna = False)
        print(bin_data)
        hist_bar(file_index, 40, whole_data_)

attribute = attributes_150[1]
figure_by_attribute(0, attribute, whole_data)

for current_file in file_path_arr:
    print("carrent file name: ", current_file)
    data = pd.read_csv(current_file, keep_default_na=False, low_memory=False)
    index_nan_by_country = data[data[attribute_1] == ''].index
    for i in index_nan_by_country:
        if data.loc[i, attribute_6] == '' and data.loc[i, attribute_7] == '' and data.loc[i, attribute_8] == '':
            data = data.drop(index = i)
    data.to_csv(current_file, index=False)

import re

def fill_region_1(file):
    data = pd.read_csv(file, keep_default_na=False, low_memory=False)
    index_nan = data[data[attribute_7] == ''].index
    for i in index_nan:
        title = data.loc[i, attributes_130[11]]
        region_1 = re.findall(r'[(](.*?)[)]', title)
        if region_1 != []:
            region_1 = region_1[0]
            data.loc[i, attribute_7] = region_1
        print(title)
        print(region_1)
    data.to_csv(file,index = False)

def fill_region_1_second(file):
    data = pd.read_csv(file, keep_default_na=False, low_memory=False)
    index_nan = data[data[attribute_7] == ''].index
    for i in index_nan:
        title = data.loc[i, attributes_130[11]]
        year = re.findall(r'[1-2][0-9]{3}', title)
        print(title)
        print(year)
        if len(year) > 0:
            year = year[0]
            region_1 = title.split(year)[1][1:]
            print(region_1)
            data.loc[i, attribute_7] = region_1
    data.to_csv(file,index = False)

def build_dict(key, value):
    dict_ = dict()
    for current_file in file_path_arr:
        data = pd.read_csv(current_file, keep_default_na=False, low_memory=False)
        index_key = data[data[value] != ''].index
        for i in index_key:
            key_ = data.loc[i, key]
            if key_ not in dict_:
                dict_[key_] = data.loc[i, value]
    return  dict_ 

winery_region_2_dict = build_dict(attribute_10, attribute_8)
In [ ]:
def fill_from_dict(current_file, dict_, key, value):
    print("current file name: ", current_file)
    cnt = 0
    data = pd.read_csv(current_file, keep_default_na=False, low_memory=False)
    index_key = data[data[value] == ''].index
    print(index_key)
    for i in index_key:
        key_ = data.loc[i, key]
        if key_ in dict_:
            data.loc[i, value] = dict_[key_]
            # print(key_, dict_[key_])
        else:
            cnt += 1

    print("There'are " + str(cnt) + "keys don't exist.")
    data.to_csv(current_file, index = False)

def figure_of_time_spent(current_data, i):
    print('')
    print('Min:', np.min(current_data))
    print('Q1:', np.percentile(current_data, 25))
    print('Q2:', np.percentile(current_data, 50))
    print('Q3:', np.percentile(current_data, 75))
    print('Max:', np.max(current_data))
    col = np.array(current_data)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 3))
    plt.boxplot(col, notch=False, vert=False)
    plt.xlabel('time spent of ' + file_path_arr[i])
    plt.show()
    outlier = np.percentile(col, 75) + (np.percentile(col, 75) - np.percentile(col, 25)) * 1.5
    print("", outlier)

def build_dict_2_key(key1, key2, value):
    dict_ = dict()
    for current_file in file_path_arr:
        data = pd.read_csv(current_file, keep_default_na=False, low_memory=False)
        index_key = data[data[key2] != ''].index
        for i in index_key:
            if data.loc[i, value] != '':
                key_ = data.loc[i, key1] + data.loc[i, key2]
                if key_ not in dict_:
                    dict_[key_] = data.loc[i, value]
    return  dict_

    print(current_data[attribute_].value_counts(dropna = False))
